info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 19 at 1:30PM PST until February 20 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Spokane
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM PST MONDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...La Crosse, Plummer, Oakesdale, Moscow, Rosalia, Pomeroy, Pullman, Potlatch, Alpowa Summit, Clarkston, Uniontown, Tekoa, Colfax, and Genesee. * WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 10 AM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Winds this strong can make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Use extra caution.
